e1033\langfenp1033\insrsid678505\cs10 :\line }{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid678505\cs10\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s44\aspalpha\aspnum\pararsid678505\ltrpar\li1327\lin1327\ri720\rin720\qj\faauto\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\charrsid678505\insrsid678505\cs10 \u8220 }{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\b\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\charrsid678505\insrsid678505\cs10 The PAMDA point}{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\b\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\charrsid678505\insrsid678505\cs10\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s44\aspalpha\aspnum\pararsid678505\ltrpar\li1327\lin1327\ri720\rin720\qj\faauto\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033{\rtlch\alang1025\afs18\ltrch\fs18\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 [39] }{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 A further criticism of the learned trial judge's approach was advanced. This point was not agitated at trial. This criticism relied upon the circumstance that the context in which the negotiations in the present case occurred included the }{\rtlch\ai\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\i\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 Property Agents and Motor Dealers Act }{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 2000 (Qld) ("the PAMDA"). This legislation requires certain formalities for the benefit of purchasers of residential land. These formalities do not impede the formation of a legally binding contract; but if these formalities are not complied with, the purchaser may, within a specified period, elect to terminate the contract.}{\rtlch\alang1025\afs16\ltrch\fs16\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 30 }{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 The argument which is put on behalf of Hebron Park is that it would be an extraordinary thing to hold a vendor bound unless and until the formalities necessary to bind the buyer irretrievably to the contract had been complied with.}{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s44\aspalpha\aspnum\pararsid678505\ltrpar\li1327\lin1327\ri720\rin720\qj\faauto\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s44\aspalpha\aspnum\pararsid678505\ltrpar\li1327\lin1327\ri720\rin720\qj\faauto\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033{\rtlch\alang1025\afs18\ltrch\fs18\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 [40] }{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 It is necessary to bear in mind that when one speaks of the intention of the parties in this field of discourse, one is speaking of the objective intention of the parties, being their "intention as expressed".}{\rtlch\alang1025\afs16\ltrch\fs16\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 31 }{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 The negotiations between the parties did not advert to the need for compliance with the PAMDA requirements. The intentions actually expressed by the parties were not qualified or conditional by any concern to observe these requirements. That this was so is hardly surprising. As Mr O'Donnell QC, who appeared with Mr Shah for Moffatt, points out, this is not a case of the kind spoken of in the relevant provisions of the PAMDA where the contract is "given to the buyer by the seller". This is not a case of a sale of a residence to a consumer but of an acquisition of stock by a developer.}{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s44\aspalpha\aspnum\pararsid678505\ltrpar\li1327\lin1327\ri720\rin720\qj\faauto\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s44\aspalpha\aspnum\pararsid678505\ltrpar\li1327\lin1327\ri720\rin720\qj\faauto\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033{\rtlch\alang1025\afs18\ltrch\fs18\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 [41] }{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe3081\langfenp3081\insrsid678505\cs10 In my respectful opinion, the unremarked existence of the formal requirements of the PAMDA do not afford a convincing basis for concluding that the parties' "intention as expressed" was not to make a legally binding agreement immediately.\u8221  (footnotes omitted)}{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033\charrsid9523022\insrsid678505\cs10\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s1\ls1\tx607\fi-323\sb240\aspalpha\aspnum\outlinelevel0\pararsid4747075\ltrpar\li607\lin607\ri0\rin0\qj\faauto\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033{\listtext\pard\plain\s1\tx607\fi-323\ltrpar\li607\lin607\ri0\rin0\ql\faauto\rtlch\ltrch\b0\i0\fs18\f0 [43]\tab }{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1986503\cs10 I will address the essential arguments raised by the respondent in turn.}{\rtlch\alang1025\afs20\ltrch\fs24\f0\lang3081\langnp3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1986503\cs10\par}\pard\plain\itap0\s1\fi0\sb240\aspalpha\aspnum\outlinelevel0\pararsid13192553\ltrpar\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\qj\faauto\rtl